    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin, China</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Conger acknowledges the Department’s telegram of the 21st, and reports that
                    he has signed the note that day (22d) after again stating the Department’s
                    views. He adds that the note will be handed on the 24th to the Chinese
                    plenipotentiaries.)</p>
            </div>
